Libyan leader Moammar Gadhafi met with Chadian President Idriss Deby , who flew into the Libyan capital in violation of U.N. sanctions , state-run television said .
Deby told the TV Saturday that he came to Libya to check on Gadhafi 's health after the Libyan leader underwent a hip operation in July .
The television report was monitored by the British Broadcasting Corporation .
Libyan television and radio said Deby arrived by air at Tripoli airport direct from the Chadian capital , Ndjamena , on Saturday , <ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">violating U.N. sanctions on Libya</ENAMEX> .
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">The sanctions prohibit air travel to and from the country except for humanitarian reasons .
The sanctions were imposed to force Libya to hand over two suspects said to have carried out the 1988 bombing of Pan Am flight 103 over Lockerbie , Scotland .
The bombing killed 270 people .</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">African leaders have denounced the sanctions , and the Organization of African Unity has said it would no longer abide by them</ENAMEX> .
Deby met with Gadhafi shortly after his arrival , and gave him a `` warm embrace which expressed the depth of African cohesion ... and the deep relations between '' Libya and Chad , the television broadcast said .
Diplomatic ties between Libya and Chad were restored in May .
Relations were severed for more than a decade when the last of the Libyan occupation troops were pushed out of Chad in 1987 .
Deby was one of the officers who forced the Libyans out of Chad .
